<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1943,2010]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1169,152,178]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1943,1969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the description and the figures of 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[859,1093,1944,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="13" refString="Li, Z. Z. &amp; Zhang, B. (2006) Description of three new species of the genus Placidus Distant from China (Hemiptera, Cidadellidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 32, 155 - 159 (In Chinese with English abstract)" type="journal article" year="2006">
Li &amp; Zhang (
<number box="[1021,1085,1944,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuoh" authorityName="Kuoh" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C. brunnea</emphasis>
(Kuoh)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the colour pattern of the head and the shape of aedeagus. However, the aedeagus figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[680,903,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" refString="Li, Z. Z. &amp; Zhang, B. (2006) Description of three new species of the genus Placidus Distant from China (Hemiptera, Cidadellidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 32, 155 - 159 (In Chinese with English abstract)" type="journal article" year="2006">
Li &amp; Zhang (
<number box="[833,895,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
seems to be damaged.
</paragraph>
